Start with the return of an award-winning reality show that follows a South African singer. Then watch a thriller about the nightmarish disappearance of a child in suburbia. Or opt for a jaw-dropping true crime story that spans 30 years. Kelly Khumalo is back for a new season of Life With Kelly Khumalo! We’ve seen ups and downs in Seasons 1 and 2. And Season 3 is promising to be quite the journey. After all, three’s a charm, right? From July 5 on Showmax.  Grief tears through Hollington Drive when 10-year-old Alex Boyd is declared missing. Sisters Theresa and Helen struggle to hold their lives and families together, as secrets begin to surface in the wake of this tragedy. Theresa is troubled by her own son’s behaviour and dreads the thought that it is possible he was somehow involved in Alex’s disappearance. Watch Hollington Drive from July 7 on BritBox.  Girl In The Picture is a true crime story of a search to solve a 30-year-old mystery: who was Sharon Marshall, and why was her real identity unknown to everyone – even her? In his international bestseller A Beautiful Child and its follow-up, Finding Sharon, award-winning investigative journalist Matt Birkbeck told the heartbreaking story of a brilliant and beautiful teenager known as Sharon Marshall. Caught in the twisted web of the monster she called her father, Sharon wasn’t her real name. On Netflix from July 6.    